article.headline: Wagner 105, Md.-Eastern Shore 86
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- James Ulrich scored 23 points to help Wagner beat Maryland-Eastern Shore 105-86 Saturday night and give coach Mike Deane his 400th career victory. Jamal Smith, who made all seven of his shots, followed with 16 points, all in the first half. Durell Vinson had 12 points and 17 rebounds for the Seahawks (7-3). Mark Porter had a career-high 13 assists. Deane, who also coached Marquette and Siena in his 24-year career, is in his fifth season at Wagner. Ed Tyson, who shot 5-for-11 on 3-pointers, led the Hawks (2-10) with 36 points.
